  "text": "# Apache Flink Windowing API Extension Points\n\n## 1. WindowAssigner Abstract Base Class\n**File:** `flink-runtime/src/main/java/org/apache/flink/streaming/api/windowing/assigners/WindowAssigner.java`\n\n**Class:** `public abstract class WindowAssigner<T, W extends Window>`\n\n**Abstract Methods (Extension Points):**\n- `Collection<W> assignWindows(T element, long timestamp, WindowAssignerContext context)` - Core method for assigning windows to elements based on element type, timestamp, and processing context\n- `Trigger<T, W> getDefaultTrigger()` - Returns the default trigger for this assigner\n- `TypeSerializer<W> getWindowSerializer(ExecutionConfig executionConfig)` - Provides serialization mechanism for windows\n- `boolean isEventTime()` - Specifies whether the assigner works with event time or processing time\n\n**Inner Class:**\n- `WindowAssignerContext` - Abstract context providing `long getCurrentProcessingTime()` method\n\n## 2. MergingWindowAssigner Subclass\n**File:** `flink-runtime/src/main/java/org/apache/flink/streaming/api/windowing/assigners/MergingWindowAssigner.java`\n\n**Class:** `public abstract class MergingWindowAssigner<T, W extends Window> extends WindowAssigner<T, W>`\n\n**Abstract Method (Merging Extension Point):**\n- `void mergeWindows(Collection<W> windows, MergeCallback<W> callback)` - Determines which windows should be merged and invokes callback with merge decisions\n\n**Inner Interface:**\n- `MergeCallback<W>` - Interface with `void merge(Collection<W> toBeMerged, W mergeResult)` method for signaling merge operations\n\n## 3. Trigger Base Class\n**File:** `flink-runtime/src/main/java/org/apache/flink/streaming/api/windowing/triggers/Trigger.java`\n\n**Class:** `public abstract class Trigger<T, W extends Window>`\n\n**Lifecycle Methods (Abstract - Extension Points):**\n- `TriggerResult onElement(T element, long timestamp, W window, TriggerContext ctx)` - Called for every element added to a pane, determines if pane should emit\n- `TriggerResult onEventTime(long time, W window, TriggerContext ctx)` - Called when event-time timer fires\n- `TriggerResult onProcessingTime(long time, W window, TriggerContext ctx)` - Called when processing-time timer fires\n- `void clear(W window, TriggerContext ctx)` - Clears trigger state for window purge\n\n**Merging Support Methods:**\n- `boolean canMerge()` - Returns true if trigger supports merging (default: false)\n- `void onMerge(W window, OnMergeContext ctx)` - Called when windows merge (default throws UnsupportedOperationException)\n\n**Context Interfaces:**\n- `TriggerContext` - Provides access to processing time, watermark, timer registration, state management\n- `OnMergeContext extends TriggerContext` - Extended context for merge operations with `mergePartitionedState()` support\n\n## 4. EventTimeSessionWindows Reference Implementation\n**File:** `flink-streaming-java/src/main/java/org/apache/flink/streaming/api/windowing/assigners/EventTimeSessionWindows.java`\n\n**Class:** `public class EventTimeSessionWindows extends MergingWindowAssigner<Object, TimeWindow>`\n\n**Key Implementation Methods:**\n- `Collection<TimeWindow> assignWindows(Object element, long timestamp, WindowAssignerContext context)` - Creates a single TimeWindow from element's timestamp to timestamp + sessionTimeout: `Collections.singletonList(new TimeWindow(timestamp, timestamp + sessionTimeout))`\n- `void mergeWindows(Collection<TimeWindow> windows, MergingWindowAssigner.MergeCallback<TimeWindow> c)` - Delegates to utility method: `TimeWindow.mergeWindows(windows, c)` which merges overlapping windows\n- `Trigger<Object, TimeWindow> getDefaultTrigger()` - Returns `EventTimeTrigger.create()`\n- `TypeSerializer<TimeWindow> getWindowSerializer(ExecutionConfig executionConfig)` - Returns `new TimeWindow.Serializer()`\n- `boolean isEventTime()` - Returns `true`\n\n**Design Pattern:** Demonstrates how to implement a session windowing strategy where window boundaries are dynamically computed based on element timestamps and session timeout gaps.\n\n## 5. TimeWindow Class\n**File:** `flink-runtime/src/main/java/org/apache/flink/streaming/api/windowing/windows/TimeWindow.java`\n\n**Class:** `public class TimeWindow extends Window`\n\n**Key Methods:**\n- Constructor: `TimeWindow(long start, long end)` - Creates window with inclusive start and exclusive end timestamps\n- `long getStart()` - Returns window start timestamp\n- `long getEnd()` - Returns window end timestamp (exclusive)\n- `long maxTimestamp()` - Returns `end - 1` (largest timestamp in window)\n- `boolean intersects(TimeWindow other)` - Checks if windows overlap: `this.start <= other.end && this.end >= other.start`\n- `TimeWindow cover(TimeWindow other)` - Returns minimal window covering both: `new TimeWindow(Math.min(start, other.start), Math.max(end, other.end))`\n\n**Utility Method:**\n- `static void mergeWindows(Collection<TimeWindow> windows, MergingWindowAssigner.MergeCallback<TimeWindow> c)` - Implements merging algorithm: sorts windows by start time and merges overlapping windows by invoking callback\n\n**Inner Class:**\n- `Serializer extends TypeSerializerSingleton<TimeWindow>` - Handles serialization of TimeWindow instances (stores two long values: start and end)\n\n## Architecture Summary\n\nFlink's windowing API provides a clean extension point architecture:\n\n1. **WindowAssigner** is the primary extension point where developers define how elements are assigned to windows\n2. **MergingWindowAssigner** extends this for session-style windows that need merging\n3. **Trigger** controls window firing behavior and supports four key lifecycle callbacks\n4. **TimeWindow** is the concrete window implementation for time-based windowing\n5. **EventTimeSessionWindows** demonstrates the complete implementation pattern combining all components\n\nDevelopers implementing custom assigners must provide:\n- Window assignment logic in `assignWindows()`\n- A default trigger in `getDefaultTrigger()`\n- Window serialization support via `getWindowSerializer()`\n- Event/Processing time semantics via `isEventTime()`\n- For merging assigners: implementation of `mergeWindows()` callback"
}

